name: graphite production | graphite | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/315/documentation

This datset represents the production of 1 kg of graphite from metamorphous rock  in ground containing graphite.;Raw material, energy and water consumption, infrastructure for the site and machineries, land use, and emissions to air are a first approximation based on limestone production.;[This dataset was already contained in the ecoinvent database version 2. It was not individually updated during the transfer to ecoinvent version 3. Life Cycle Impact Assessment results may still have changed, as they are affected by changes in the supply chain, i.e. in other datasets. This dataset was generated following the ecoinvent quality guidelines for version 2. It may have been subject to central changes described in the ecoinvent version 3 change report (http://www.ecoinvent.org/database/ecoinvent-version-3/reports-of-changes/), and the results of the central updates were reviewed extensively. The changes added e.g. consistent water flows and other information throughout the database. The documentation of this dataset can be found in the ecoinvent reports of version 2, which are still available via the ecoinvent website. The change report linked above covers all central changes that were made during the conversion process.]

 From metamorphous rock  in the ground containing graphite.

This activites ends with the production of 1 kg of graphite. The dataset includes raw materials, machineries, energy consumption, emissions to air, and infrastructure of the site. The dataset doesn't include emissions to water.

exchanges.description:
Graphite is besides diamonds and fullerenes the third crystalline form of carbon. It occurs naturally in metamorphic rocks or can be produced artificially from different types of carbon sources (often used are petroleum coke and charcoal). In nature, graphite occures in three different forms - as flakes, as lump and amorphous
